name: Nine: Nine Time Travels
overview: Park Sun-Woo works as an anchorman at a TV broadcasting station. He is in love with newsreporter Joo Min-Young, who is bright and honest. Park Sun-Woo then obtains 9 incense items, which allows him to go back 20 years in time. Park Sun-Woo travels to the past.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Anchorman Park Sun Woo heads to Nepal to identify the body of his dead older brother, who's been on an adventure to help restore their family's happiness.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Despite his worsening condition, Sun Woo and CBM work together to expose Choi Jin Cheol. Meanwhile Min Young learns the truth.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Realizing that the incense sticks are the key to time travel, Sun Woo follows his brother's clues to find the nine remaining incense sticks.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: It's Christmas 2012, and Sun woo surprises his mother and his best friend with a gift and a secret. His actions in the past begin to affect his present and his memory.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Now with his brother happily married and alive, Sun Woo must face the consequences of no longer having Min Young by his side.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Sun Woo's illness worsens with each travel back in time, but he's still determined to save his father's life.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Sun Woo thinks he's saved his father's life, but an unexpected turn of events shows that he's still died, and Sun Woo is nowhere closer to discovering the killer.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Some secrets are better left in the past, but Sun Woo's stubbornness to find out the truth becomes the end of him.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Without the incense sticks, Sun Woo's fate is now in the hands of Young Hoon.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: Min Young becomes increasingly confused when her memories of Sun Woo get mixed up with her former self. Sun Woo realizes he doesn't know what his past self is thinking anymore.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: Sun Woo denies any of Min Young's memories, even though she knows they were lovers before.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: In order to get their lives back to normal, Sun Woo tells his brother the whole truth, and hopes he'll accept his true fate.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview: Sun Woo's visit to young Jung Woo is unsuccessful when Choi Jin Cheol's hired man stabs him in the abdomen.

episodes.name: Episode 14
episodes.overview: Chaos erupts when the truth of Sun Woo and Min Young's illicit relationship comes to light.

episodes.name: Episode 15
episodes.overview: Sun Woo begins to self-destruct after he finds it too difficult to deal with the changes he brought on by altering the past.

episodes.name: Episode 16
episodes.overview: Choi Jin Cheol discovers Sun Woo's secret, and uses the incense stick to get rid of Sun Woo once and for all.

episodes.name: Episode 17
episodes.overview: With his life on the line, Sun Woo uses the last incense stick to save young Sun Woo, and stop his brother's wedding.

episodes.name: Episode 18
episodes.overview: It's the day of Min Young and Sun Woo's wedding.

episodes.name: Episode 19
episodes.overview: Jung Woo and Young Hoon desperately search for Sun Woo's body, in the present and in 1993.

episodes.name: Episode 20
episodes.overview: With Sun Woo's death in 1993, he sets off a chain of events that affects his new future self.
